description:
&lt;p&gt;The Community &amp; Mental Health Division are excited to recruit an Education, Health &amp; Care Plan (EHCP) Coordinator for children and young people with Special Educational Needs and/or Disability (SEND). The Children and Families Act 2014 set out new legislation which brought about changes to support improving outcomes for children and young people with SEND. This newly established administrative post will support the organisations key role of providing health advice for children and young people undergoing assessment for Education, Health and Care Plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have exceptional organisational skills and be able to forge strong, professional relationships will colleagues from a range of professional backgrounds across the Trust and externally with partners in Local Authorities and education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position can be based at any of our community sites: Innovation Park, Liverpool/Sefton Carers Centre, Waterloo/Houghton Street, Southport.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Lindsey Marlton (Service Manager) on 0151 252 5623&lt;/p&gt;
